cs.DB, cs.IR, cs.DS, cs.AI, cs.LG. 

The paper deals with the problem of efficiently indexing and searching RDF data, which is a common task in database systems and information retrieval. Therefore, cs.DB (Database) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval) are the most likely categories. The paper proposes a trie-based index layout, which is a data structure commonly used in computer science for efficient string matching and searching, suggesting cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) as another likely category. The paper also introduces novel techniques to reduce the space of representation, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.LG (Machine Learning).
